node.text: It is beautiful to watch the joy in Jon and even more the joy captured in these video clips when Jon’s parents came to visit this week. It was a special treat for Jon as they don’t live nearby but, as you notice in the video, Jon clearly wants to show his parents how hard he works and how far he has come.  I speak of this often; the purity of Jon and the love that radiates from him is like nothing of this world.  I know God has big plans for Jon!

node.text:
As many of you know I have frequently posted about the CBD #staystrongjonnygrant that was started about a year ago.  I want to first note that I was very hesitant to promote a product on my page since my purpose has always been to share awareness and hope to others on this platform. But, because of the impact this formula and the team behind this product have played in Jon’s healing, I felt the need to share this in hopes of helping others.

This is a short video interview with the owner, Tom, of the CBD company that @dr.kyledaigledc @bcrawforddc @cdrmrk worked hand and hand with to produce this product.  These doctors true mission is to help others.   Each of them have worked intensively with Jon and because of the bond & relationship created they felt called to name the formula after Jon. And they gratuitously designate a percentage of the proceeds to the continued healing process of Jon.

Side note: I personally love the Fobo Berry CBD energy drink ❤

node.text:
Hope everyone is having a wonderful weekend.  This song speaks to my soul.  The journey of life is one of experiences and faith in God.  We do not always understand our circumstances but when we keep our eyes focused on the Lord we find peace.

One of the biggest challenges is waiting on the Lord when all else feels like it is crumbling around us.  Through this journey with Jon I can say, without a doubt, waiting on God’s timing and not our own brought forth unimaginable blessings.

The song in this clip was just released by @elevationworship and @maverickcitymusic in their knew album Old Church Basement.  This particular song is called Wait on You. Jon and I have been listening to it in repeat this weekend.  Such powerful words of truth.

#staystrongjonnygrant

Many ask if Jon gets tired of doing exercises & therapy...great question. Jon pushes himself.  Whenever I ask him if he wants to rest or take a nap the response I get “no sleep.” Jon has always had a drive and the ability to push the limits. For the first two years after his injury, Jon would stay in bed 23 out of 24 hours a day. I kept believing that when Jon was ready and given the right tools he would fight.  Jon is the driver of his recovery.

Thankfully he wears himself out enough that he sleeps like a baby which, as those that are caregivers know, is a blessing.  There was a time he didn’t sleep and those nights lead to tough days.  I guess the message I am trying to share is Jon is leading his recovery. I give him the options and allow him to steer the ship.

#staystrongjonnygrant

node.text:
Each of us are here on earth for a certain purpose.  I believe God prepared me for this journey with Jon. Definitely not an easy one, but I know without a doubt I wouldn’t want Jon to have to go through this alone.

One of the most challenging aspects of being a caregiver to a love one with a brain injury is to remain patient in the process.  Many times this process of healing takes time: in our case years.  Watching the one I love go through this journey is heartbreaking at times, but it is my purpose to stand strong with love, no matter what obstacles we encounter or how long it takes to achieve milestone, I will stand right here with him.

When I released control and gave God the space for His hands to move mountains we found peace and joy in our new life. No matter the time it takes we trust & believe that God has gone before us and is guiding our way.

#staystrongjonnygrant

This was a pretty cool breakthrough today @apexbraincenters.

The technique explained at the end of the video is one where warm or cold water is put into the ears to assess and activate certain responses of the inner ear and eye movement systems.

What @neurowellnessdoc chose to do specifically with Jon had a lasting effect of stopping his problematic eye movements for about 90 minutes. Notice how stable Jon’s eyes are at the end of the video. 

Disclaimer: seek the advice and evaluation of a qualified profession - do not try this at home

Here’s another video from the weekend when @bcrawforddc @dr.kyledaigledc and @drrobertmelillo came to visit to update Jon’s clinical protocols. In this video we really focus on how we have used laser therapy under the guidance of @bcrawforddc. Dr Crawford’s novel approach to the use of laser therapy for brain rehab has helped us speed up Jon’s recovery.  These approaches are being applied to many different types of brain injuries with a high degree of positive results.  I think the main thing to highlight from this conversation with Dr Crawford is that there are very few modalities that offer so many positive benefits with little to no adverse effects.

We are very thankful to have had these tools especially early on in recovery as the lasers served as great passive modalities that improved Jon’s brain inflammation and function to a point that we were able to do more with him. 

If you are curious and want to look into laser therapy or purchase a laser, reach out to Dr Crawford and Dr Daigle’s new company @neuro_solutions here: www.neuro-solution.com or email them at info@neuro-solution.com

node.text: It is beautiful to watch the joy in Jon and even more the joy captured in these video clips when Jon’s parents came to visit this week. It was a special treat for Jon as they don’t live nearby but, as you notice in the video, Jon clearly wants to show his parents how hard he works and how far he has come.  I speak of this often; the purity of Jon and the love that radiates from him is like nothing of this world.  I know God has big plans for Jon!

node.text:
Jon continues to blow me away.  He is driven day to day and moment to moment, to live in the now of his circumstances with such joy & peace. 

This video represents so much about this journey.  The obstacles Jon has faced to get to this moment & ability is hard to even share without writing a book.  Though this exercise is small to many there is so much taking place. There was not even a chance this was possible months ago.  I also feel the depth of determination & challenge this exercises takes for Jon. I find myself wanting to take a depth breath for him or even interrupt his brain processing as he works through this. One of the biggest lessons I have learned is the best thing I can do as a caregiver & wife is allow Jon to experience the journey.  It is through the journey that we grow.  Finding the awareness of helping verses interfering with the process.

“What is coming will make sense of what is happening now.  Let God finish his work. Let the composer complete his symphony” Max Lucado

Side Note: Jon got his retainer today.  I will share what it looks like to those that were interested in a previous post.

As many of you know I have frequently posted about the CBD #staystrongjonnygrant that was started about a year ago.  I want to first note that I was very hesitant to promote a product on my page since my purpose has always been to share awareness and hope to others on this platform. But, because of the impact this formula and the team behind this product have played in Jon’s healing, I felt the need to share this in hopes of helping others.

This is a short video interview with the owner, Tom, of the CBD company that @dr.kyledaigledc @bcrawforddc @cdrmrk worked hand and hand with to produce this product.  These doctors true mission is to help others.   Each of them have worked intensively with Jon and because of the bond & relationship created they felt called to name the formula after Jon. And they gratuitously designate a percentage of the proceeds to the continued healing process of Jon.

Side note: I personally love the Fobo Berry CBD energy drink ❤

I believe I have mentioned this in a previous post: neurological grinding. 

This past year @supremiadentistry fitted Jon for a night time guard that has helped tremendously.  We soon realized the grinding & clenching of his jaw was taking place during the day as well.  It is now time to address this issue.

In this clip a tens unit is being used to relax Jon’s jaw muscles.  Then Dr. Suh measured a ‘resting position’ for him where his muscles were the most relaxed. At the same time Dr. Suh was recording that position for the lab so he can make Jon an appliance that will help calm his jaw muscles. 

Thank you @supremiadentistry for helping navigate this part of Jon’s healing journey.

#staystrongjonnygrant

Jon was a very handy man that could do just about anything.  I do miss that part of him sometimes but thankful for those like David and my dad that help in those areas.

This weekend we started tackling the garage.  There is still so much to go through but we made a small dent.

Thank you David for all your help this past weekend.

#staystrongjonnygrant
